==English==
===Etymology===
Coined by Australian [[journalist]] and [[politician]] [[w:Daniel Deniehy|Daniel Deniehy]] (1828-1865) in 1853 [[satirise|satirising]] a proposal of [[w:William Wentworth|William Wentworth]] for an [[hereditary]] [[peerage]] in the then colony of [[New South Wales]].
===Noun===
# {{AU}} A [[peerage]] (hypothetical or proposed) in [[Australia]].  The term is used [[scorn|scornfully]] for such a scheme.
#: 1853: ''we all know the common water mole was transferred into the duck-billed platypus, and in some distant emulation of this degeneration, I suppose we are to be favoured with a "bunyip aristocracy"'' &mdash; [[w:Daniel Deniehy|Daniel Deniehy]], [[w:Sydney Morning Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]] 16 August 1853